<subSubSection id="C45C5AD90E7F8886D2690328C94EE5B8" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A9C17AC808E20EB3009CAF25C16E779" pageNumber="59">Discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="618892CCA6D0EDB74C9BDF7926546EFC" pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicName id="B3689AD67CD5EC7C9289EC0473B3E1ED" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:238041" authority="Yamane, Tuan Viet Bui &amp; Eguchi, 2008" authorityName="Yamane, Tuan Viet Bui &amp; Eguchi" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Opamyrma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Opamyrma Yamane, Bui &amp; Eguchi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Opamyrma</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="50A73AEBBE4A5A06E719967C5DE4A862" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:2355" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Apomyrma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Apomyrma Brown, Gotwald &amp; Lévieux" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Apomyrma</taxonomicName>
with several shared characteristics: the outer face of the labrum bears peg-like teeth; the frontal lobe is absent; the antennal socket is directed almost dorsad; the sternite of the petiole is reduced to a small posteroventral sclerite, bounded by the conspicuous tergo-sternal sutures; and the third abdominal segment above the helcium has a free anterior face. All this may support the inclusion of the 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A0096FB550D811545BCE12A8A043D3AD" rank="genus">new genus</taxonomicNameLabel>
within the separate tribe 
<taxonomicName id="0C7C662130DFDB8B3BE241A2F4E460A8" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:183163" lsidName-HNS="Apomyrmini Dlussky &amp; Fedoseeva" pageNumber="59" rank="tribe" tribe="Apomyrmini">Apomyrmini</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="FD7218CB3E04D5D0A2CBD279F7E0DA67" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:2355" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Apomyrma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Apomyrma Brown, Gotwald &amp; Lévieux" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Apomyrma</taxonomicName>
(but see below for the current status of this tribe).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
